channel.title: Plzz help!
channel.description: Okay. I believe that i have done everything. First I downloaded a server source. Then, I downloaded "No-ip." I made a host on the "No-ip" website. Next, I logged into my router and tried to port forward. I have a Netgear WGT624v3 Router. I went into the "Port Forwarding/Port Triggering" tab. Then I clicked add service. For the name, I put my server name. I kept it at "TCP/UDP." For the starting port, I put 43594. For the ending one, I also put 43594. I put in an IP and then I clicked "Apply." Next, I went into the source and changed The name, my rights, etc. I compiled it and clicked run server. The command prompt came up and it said, "Starting up (My server name) on 0.0.0.0:43594..." But nothing happened after that. Can anyone help me?
